{"lemma":"شَكْلِ","slug":"شَكْلِ","root":"ش.ك.ل","root_slug":"ش-ك-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ك-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَكْل","root":"شكل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":22},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22842","n22843","n22848","n22849","n22850"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%92%D9%84%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to hobble (an animal)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to vocalize (a text)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become dubious or confused"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become dubious or confused"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to form"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to form, to fashion, to figure, to shape, to sculpture, to picture"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pose","examples":[{"text":"يشكِّلون تهديدًا على بلده.","english":"They pose a threat to his country."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَكَلَ (šakala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"likeness, resemblance, semblance"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"model, pattern, mode, manner"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"shape, form, figure"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kind, sort, variety"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"way, course, mode, manner of acting; conduct"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"aim, intention, purpose"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"something suitable, fit or proper for someone"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vocalization of a text"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a species of plant, yellow and red in color"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"coquettishness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَكَلَ (šakala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dubious or confused matter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"an ear ornament of pearl or silver"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of شِكَال (šikāl, “hobble”)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22842","headword_ar":"شَكَلَ","root":"$kl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as an intrans. verb: see 4, in three places. ―         -b2-  And see 5.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akala Alfarasa biAl$~ikaAli","text_ar":"شَكَلَ الفَرَسَ بِالشِّكَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akala Ald~aAb~apa","text_ar":"شَكَلَ الدَّابَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akolN","text_ar":"شَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beast, with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAl","text_ar":"شِكَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he bound the legs of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beast with the rope called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAl","text_ar":"شِكَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ak~alahaA","text_ar":"شَكَّلَهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$okiylN","text_ar":"تَشْكِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akalotu AlT~aAy^ira","text_ar":"شَكَلْتُ الطَّايِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I bound the legs of the bird in like manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akalotu Eani AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"شَكَلْتُ عَنِ البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I bound the camel's"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAl","text_ar":"شِكَال"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the fore girth and the hind girth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I put"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the hind girth and the fore girth of the camel, a cord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"string, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAl","text_ar":"شِكَال"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then bound it, in order that the hind girth might not become"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"too"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near to the sheath of the penis."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hqb","text_ar":"حقب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  And [hence, i. e.] from the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAl","text_ar":"شِكَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the beast, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akala AlkitaAba","text_ar":"شَكَلَ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AHát, S, Msb, K, TA,) inf. n. as above, (Msb, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He restricted"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the meaning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pronunciation of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the writing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qay~adahu","text_ar":"قَيَّدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", AHát, S, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he marked the writing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolamahu","text_ar":"اَعْلَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the signs of the desinential syntax"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHát, * S, * Msb, TA *) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the other syllabical signs and the diacritical points"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamahu","text_ar":"اَعْجَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) but AHát says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akala AlkitaAba","text_ar":"شَكَلَ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the former meaning; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojamahu","text_ar":"اَعْجَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he dotted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pointed, it"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the diacritical points"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAba","text_ar":"الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$kl","text_ar":"اشكل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akalahu","text_ar":"شَكَلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K, TA;) as though [meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he removed from it dubiousness and confusion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA;) so that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case is to denote privation: (TA:) this [J says (TA)] I have transcribed from a book, without having heard it. (S.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akalato $aEorahaA","text_ar":"شَكَلَتْ شَعْرَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; thus correctly, as pointed by IKtt; accord. to the K ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$k~lt","text_ar":"شكّلت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaited two locks of her hair, of the fore part of her head, on the right and left,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and then bound with them her other"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*awaAy^ib","text_ar":"ذَوَايِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pendent locks"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plaits"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$kl","text_ar":"شكل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus in the TA, so that it may be either"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akala","text_ar":"شَكَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$k~l","text_ar":"شكّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the lion)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compressed"},{"kind":"text","text":"the lioness: on the authority of IKtt. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akilato","text_ar":"شَكِلَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akalN","text_ar":"شَكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a woman)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"used amorous gesture"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaviour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such gesture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaviour, with coquettish boldness, and feigned coyness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposition; displayed what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikol","text_ar":"شِكْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoj","text_ar":"غُنْج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dal~","text_ar":"دَلّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazal","text_ar":"غَزَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$k~lt","text_ar":"تشكّلت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[signifies the same], i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tadal~alato","text_ar":"تَدَلَّلَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and in like manner"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t$k~l","text_ar":"تشكّل"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said of a man]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akalN","text_ar":"شَكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below, in two places. ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akilotu A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"شَكِلْتُ اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k","text_ar":"ك"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakanotu","text_ar":"رَكَنْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I inclined to such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trusted to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relied upon, it, so as to be,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become, easy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet, in mind"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","O"]},{"entry_id":"n22843","headword_ar":"شكّل","root":"$kl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", as an intrans. verb: see 4: ―         -b2-  and see also 5.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$k~lhu","text_ar":"شكّلهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$okiylN","text_ar":"تَشْكِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He formed, fashioned, figured, shaped, sculptured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pictured, it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saw~arahu","text_ar":"صَوَّرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) namely, a thing. (TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 1, in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22848","headword_ar":"شَكْلٌ","root":"$kl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abapN","text_ar":"شَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A likeness, resemblance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"semblance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a well-known signification of the latter word, but one which I do not find unequivocally assigned to it in its proper art. in any of the lexicons]. (AA, K, TA. [In the CK, and in my MS. copy of the K, in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~abahu","text_ar":"الشَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the first explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~akolu","text_ar":"الشَّكْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K accord. to the TA, we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ibohu","text_ar":"الشِّبْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but that the explanation which I have given is correct, is shown by what here follows.]) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY fulaAnK $akolN mino A^abiyhi","text_ar":"فِى فُلَانٍ شَكْلٌ مِنْ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In such a one is a likeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resemblance, of his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (AA, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino A^abiyhi","text_ar":"مِنْ اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi A^a$okalapN","text_ar":"فِيهِ اَشْكَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ukolapN","text_ar":"شُكْلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1587},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkilN","text_ar":"شَاكِلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K, TA,) [likewise] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AA, O, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$aAbahapN","text_ar":"مُشَابَهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TK:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkilapN","text_ar":"شَاكِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akolN","text_ar":"شَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K, TA;) [for] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA EalaY $aAkilapi","text_ar":"هٰذَا عَلَى شَاكِلَةِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiyhi","text_ar":"اَبِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahihi","text_ar":"شَبَهِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is accordant to the likeness of his father"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivaAlN","text_ar":"مِثَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA EalaY $akoli h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا عَلَى شَكْلِ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivaAlihi","text_ar":"مِثَالِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is according to the model,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pattern,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of this"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shape, form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suwrap","text_ar":"صُورَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a thing;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is perceived by the senses;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is imagined:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"form"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayoy^ap","text_ar":"هَيْيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), of a body,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused by the entire contents' being included by one boundary, as in the case of a sphere;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by several boundaries, as in those bodies that have several angles"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides, such as have four"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as have six"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]: so says Ibn-El-Kemál: (TA:) pl. [of pauc., in this and in other senses,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$okaAlN","text_ar":"اَشْكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ukuwlN","text_ar":"شُكُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b4-  [It often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind, sort,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of animals, plants, food, &c.] ―         -b5-  [And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"likeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of the actions"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a person:] it is said in a trad. respecting the description of the Prophet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA^alotu","text_ar":"سَاَلْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiY Eano $akolihi","text_ar":"اَبِى عَنْ شَكْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I asked my father respecting the likeness of his actions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting what was like his actions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to IAmb: or, accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"respecting his particular way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkilapN","text_ar":"شَاكِلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise, and more commonly,] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a particular way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA;) as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kul~N yaEomalu EalaY $aAkilatihi","text_ar":"كُلٌّ يَعْمَلُ عَلَى شَاكِلَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, TA,) in the Kur [xvii. 86], (O, TA,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Every one does according to his particular way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (Ibn-'Arafeh, S, O, Bd, Jel, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is suitable to his state in respect of right direction"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of error,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the essential nature of his soul, and to his circumstances that are consequent to the constitution,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temperament, of his body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to his nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"natural disposition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, Er-Rághib, O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which he is restricted"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as with a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikaAl","text_ar":"شِكَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Er-Rághib, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his direction towards which he would go:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, O, K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his side"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that he takes"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Katádeh, O, K, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his aim, intention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purpose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Katádeh, O, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akolN","text_ar":"شَكْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aim, intention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purpose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSodN","text_ar":"قَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b6-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is suitable"},{"kind":"text","text":"to one; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for one: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA mino hawaAYa wamino $akoliY","text_ar":"هٰذَا مِنْ هَوَاىَ وَمِنْ شَكْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is of what is loved by me and of what is suitable to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa $akoluhu mino $akoliY","text_ar":"لَيْسَ شَكْلُهُ مِنْ شَكْلِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is suitable to him is not of what is suitable to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [And hence, app.,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA$akoliY wa$akoluhu","text_ar":"مَاشَكْلِى وَشَكْلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is my case and"},{"kind":"text","text":"[what is]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its, case?"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of his, or its, remoteness from me. (T and TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~N","text_ar":"اُمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-  And sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$okaAlN","text_ar":"اَشْكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, TA) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Discordant affairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"objects of want, concerning things on account of which one imposes upon himself difficulty and for which one is anxious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dubious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confused, affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discordant, and dubious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confused, affairs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$ak~alap","text_ar":"المُشَكَّلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almu$okilap","text_ar":"المُشْكِلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivolN","text_ar":"مِثْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ikolN","text_ar":"شِكْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like"},{"kind":"text","text":"of another"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constitution:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb: [and accord. to Er-Rághib, it seems that the attribute properly denoted by it is congruity between two persons in respect of the way or manner of acting or conduct: but in the passage in which this is expressed in the TA, I find erasures and alterations which render it doubtful:]) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$okaAlN","text_ar":"اَشْكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ukuwlN","text_ar":"شُكُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as above]. (S, O, Msb, K. *) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA $akolu h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا شَكْلُ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the like of this."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN $akolu fulaAnK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ شَكْلُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the like of such a one in his several states"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conditions"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]. (TA.) In the saying in the Kur [xxxviii. 58],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA=xaru mino $akolihi","text_ar":"وَا=خَرُ مِنْ شَكْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And other"},{"kind":"text","text":"punishment"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the like thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, TA,) Mujáhid read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn $ikolihi","text_ar":"من شِكْلِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.)       -A3-  Also sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$okaAlN","text_ar":"اَشْكَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying, (O, K,) accord. to IAar, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain ornaments"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of pearls"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling one another, worn as ear-drops by women:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or, as some say, the sing. signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain thing which girls,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young women, used to append to their hair, of pearls"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of silver."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of plant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversified in colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow and red."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.)       -A5-  [And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"various syllabical signs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vowel-points &c., by which the pronunciation of words is indicated and restricted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"originally an inf. n., and therefore thus used in a pl. sense.]       -A6-  See also the next paragraph."}],"source_refs":["AA","TA","O","K","TK","S","Bd","L","Lth","Zj","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n22849","headword_ar":"شِكْلٌ","root":"$kl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph, latter part, in two places.       -A2-  Also, as an attribute of a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Amorous gesture"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaviour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such gesture,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaviour, combined with coquettish boldness, and feigned coyness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opposition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dal~N","text_ar":"دَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunojN","text_ar":"غُنْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazalN","text_ar":"غَزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K; [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gazol","text_ar":"غَزْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a mistranscription;]) or her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gunoj","text_ar":"غُنْج"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comely"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dal~","text_ar":"دَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby a woman renders herself comely"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleasing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akolN","text_ar":"شَكْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (K.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN *aAtu $ikolK","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ ذَاتُ شِكْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman having amorous gesture"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"behaviour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, O, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n22850","headword_ar":"شَكَلٌ","root":"$kl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", in a sheep or goat, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality of being white in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAkilap","text_ar":"شَاكِلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O. [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$okalu","text_ar":"اَشْكَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) [In this sense, accord. to the TK, an inf. n., of which the verb is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akila","text_ar":"شَكِلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a ram &c.]. ―         -b2-  And in an eye, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality of having what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ukolap","text_ar":"شُكْلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, O.) [Accord. to the TK, in this sense also an inf. n., of which the verb is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$akila","text_ar":"شَكِلَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a thing, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It had a redness in its whiteness."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}